{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1774471797,"nonce":"hyfnAvIcq2CoWgf1jJGAtV+8rmM=","message":"**Root cause found: JAX arrays stored as static PyTree metadata in feedbax model**\n\nFeedbax's model construction (models.py, bodies.py, channel.py) stores JAX arrays as static (auxiliary) data in several Module fields. Warnings confirm: \"A JAX array is being set as static! This can result in unexpected behavior.\"\n\nWhen the model is passed to eqx.filter_jit, these static arrays become part of the JIT cache key. The controller gradient update (eqx.apply_updates) changes array leaf values, but the static arrays may also change or be reconstructed with different identity — causing the JIT to see a new cache key and recompile.\n\nCounts:\n- task: 50 static leaves (22 callables, 28 other)\n- loss_func: 26 static leaves (15 callables, 11 other)\n- model: 112 static leaves (9 callables, 103 other)\n\nThe fix must be in feedbax: ensure JAX arrays in model/task Modules are dynamic leaves, not static aux_data. The warnings come from models.py:82, models.py:99, bodies.py:177, channel.py:137, bodies.py:190, bodies.py:200, intervention_compat.py:56.\n\nShort-term workaround: use jax.jit with manual partitioning that excludes the model's static arrays from the cache key, or pass the model pre-partitioned (dynamic only) to the JIT functions.","files":null}]}